class: middle

# Pick a purpose

---


## Segmented bar plots can be hard to read

.panelset[

.panel[.panel-name[Plot]

::: {.cell layout-align="center"}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![](u2-d14-effective-dataviz_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-16-1.png){fig-align='center' width=60%}
:::
:::

]

.panel[.panel-name[Code]


::: {.cell layout-align="center"}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(brexit, aes(y = region, fill = opinion)) + #<<
  geom_bar()
```
:::

]

]


---

## Use facets

.panelset[

.panel[.panel-name[Plot]
::: {.cell layout-align="center"}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![](u2-d14-effective-dataviz_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-17-1.png){fig-align='center' width=90%}
:::
:::
]

.panel[.panel-name[Code]

::: {.cell layout-align="center"}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(brexit, aes(y = opinion, fill = region)) +
  geom_bar() +
  facet_wrap(~region, nrow = 1) #<<
```
:::
]

]

---


## Avoid redundancy?


::: {.cell layout-align="center"}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![](u2-d14-effective-dataviz_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-18-1.png){fig-align='center' width=90%}
:::
:::

---

## Redundancy can help tell a story

.panelset[

.panel[.panel-name[Plot]
::: {.cell layout-align="center"}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![](u2-d14-effective-dataviz_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-19-1.png){fig-align='center' width=90%}
:::
:::
]

.panel[.panel-name[Code]

::: {.cell layout-align="center"}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(brexit, aes(y = opinion, fill = opinion)) +
  geom_bar() +
  facet_wrap(~region, nrow = 1)
```
:::
]

]

---


## Be selective with redundancy

.panelset[

.panel[.panel-name[Plot]

::: {.cell layout-align="center"}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![](u2-d14-effective-dataviz_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-20-1.png){fig-align='center' width=90%}
:::
:::

]

.panel[.panel-name[Code]


::: {.cell layout-align="center"}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(brexit, aes(y = opinion, fill = opinion)) +
  geom_bar() +
  facet_wrap(~region, nrow = 1) +
  guides(fill = "none") #<<
```
:::

]

]


---

## Use informative labels

.panelset[

.panel[.panel-name[Plot]
::: {.cell layout-align="center"}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![](u2-d14-effective-dataviz_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-21-1.png){fig-align='center' width=90%}
:::
:::
]

.panel[.panel-name[Code]

::: {.cell layout-align="center"}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(brexit, aes(y = opinion, fill = opinion)) +
  geom_bar() +
  facet_wrap(~region, nrow = 1) +
  guides(fill = "none") +
  labs(
    title = "Was Britain right/wrong to vote to leave EU?", #<<
    x = NULL, y = NULL
  )
```
:::
]

]

---


## A bit more info

.panelset[

.panel[.panel-name[Plot]

::: {.cell layout-align="center"}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![](u2-d14-effective-dataviz_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-22-1.png){fig-align='center' width=90%}
:::
:::

]

.panel[.panel-name[Code]


::: {.cell layout-align="center"}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(brexit, aes(y = opinion, fill = opinion)) +
  geom_bar() +
  facet_wrap(~region, nrow = 1) +
  guides(fill = "none") +
  labs(
    title = "Was Britain right/wrong to vote to leave EU?",
    subtitle = "YouGov Survey Results, 2-3 September 2019", #<<
    caption = "Source: https://d25d2506sfb94s.cloudfront.net/cumulus_uploads/document/x0msmggx08/YouGov%20-%20Brexit%20and%202019%20election.pdf", #<<
    x = NULL, y = NULL
  )
```
:::

]

]


---

## Let's do better

.panelset[

.panel[.panel-name[Plot]
::: {.cell layout-align="center"}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![](u2-d14-effective-dataviz_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-23-1.png){fig-align='center' width=90%}
:::
:::
]

.panel[.panel-name[Code]

::: {.cell layout-align="center"}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(brexit, aes(y = opinion, fill = opinion)) +
  geom_bar() +
  facet_wrap(~region, nrow = 1) +
  guides(fill = "none") +
  labs(
    title = "Was Britain right/wrong to vote to leave EU?",
    subtitle = "YouGov Survey Results, 2-3 September 2019",
    caption = "Source: bit.ly/2lCJZVg", #<<
    x = NULL, y = NULL
  )
```
:::
]

]

---


## Fix up facet labels

.panelset[

.panel[.panel-name[Plot]

::: {.cell layout-align="center"}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![](u2-d14-effective-dataviz_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-24-1.png){fig-align='center' width=90%}
:::
:::

]

.panel[.panel-name[Code]


::: {.cell layout-align="center"}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(brexit, aes(y = opinion, fill = opinion)) +
  geom_bar() +
  facet_wrap(~region,
    nrow = 1,
    labeller = label_wrap_gen(width = 12) #<<
  ) + 
  guides(fill = "none") +
  labs(
    title = "Was Britain right/wrong to vote to leave EU?",
    subtitle = "YouGov Survey Results, 2-3 September 2019",
    caption = "Source: bit.ly/2lCJZVg",
    x = NULL, y = NULL
  )
```
:::

]

]


